Title: The Body Keeps the Score: Brain, Mind, and Body in the Healing of Trauma
Author: Bessel A. van der Kolk
My Review: This is an INCREDIBLE book. I knew of trauma, but I had no inkling of its astonishingly multivariable effects on the brain and body. This book radically helped me understand the people in my life who have experienced trauma. Much like Oliver Sack's style of writing, Dr. van der Kolk mixes anecdotes from his clinical experience with broader discussions of the research around and public policy affecting trauma victims. It is very effective and engaging.
